======= Creating Files and folders ========
touch file1 -> create empty file
touch -/downloads/file1 -> create empty file in specific directory/folder
echo "hello" > file1.txt -> create file and write into file
mkdir abc -> create empty dir or folder
mkdir -/downloads/xyz -> creating xyz folder in specific dir/folder
mkdir -p abc/xyz/123 -> create directory in a path
mkdir abc xyz -> create multiple folder
mkdir "abc zxc" -> crete folder with space name
mkdir "ABC_XCZ" -> create folder with symbol name
mkdir "AXC BNM" -> create folder with capital letter name 

mkdir {a,b,c,d,e,f}_{1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9}  -> create multiple folder in a single command 
mkdir {a,b,c,d,e,f}_{1..9}  -> create multiple folder in a single command 
Touch {a,b,c,d,e,f}_{1..9}/file{1..100}  -> create multiple files in a multiple folder with a single command
ls {a,b,c,d,e,f}_{1..9}/file{1..100}  -> show multiple files in a multiple folder with a single command

======= delete Files and folders ========

rm file1.txt  -> delete a file
rm -/downloads/file.txt -> delete file in directory from home directory
rm file1.txt -/downloads/file.txt -> delete multiple file
rm *.txt -> delete all txt files
rm file* -> delete all file that name start with file
rm *4* -> delete all file that have 4 in their name

rm -r sharma -> delete a folder
rm -r sharma/ -> delete a folder and inside all thing in it
rm -ri sharma/ -> delete a folder and inside all thing in it but before delete it confirm 
rmdir sharma -> delete a folder/directory

======= copy Files and folders ========
cp file.txt file2.txt -> copy from file 1 to file 2


======= moving & rename Files and folders ========
mv file1.txt file2.txt  -> rename from file 1 to file2
mv vishal/ vishal  -> rename a folder
mv -/desktop/vis -/downloads/ -> move folder from one dir to another dir

======= editing Files by nano ========
nano file1.txt -> create and edit a file through nano
we cam use many option in nano editor 

======= Locate command ========
locate *.log -> find all log files in our system
sudo updatedb -> add files in db to find through locate

======= Find command ========
find -> show all files & folders in cureent directories
find /home/vis/downloads/noida -> find folder
find . -maxdepth 1 -> show level 1 all folder and files
find . -maxdepth 4 -tyde d  -> show level 4 all folders 
find . -name "5.txt" -> search 5.txt file by name
find . -name "*.txt" -> search all .txt file by name
find . -iname "*.txt" -> search all .txt file by case senstative name
sudo find / -type f -size +100k  -> search all files that have more than 100 KB size
sudo find / -type f -size -100k -o -size +5M | wc -l -> find files count by size

======= Viewing Files ========
cat file1.txt -> show content in file1
cat file[1-5].txt > file6 -> show all 1 to 5 files content in file 6
cat file[1-5].txt | tac -> reverse content vertically
cat file[1-5].txt | head -n 2  -> show top 2 lines


======= Sorting Data ========
sort word.txt > sorted.txt  -> sort content with alphabetic
sort -r word.txt   -> reverse txt 
ls -l /etc | head -n 20 | sort -k 5nr  - >sort files in etc folder

======== File Archiving and Compression ==========
tar -cvf abc.tar file[1-3].txt  -> archieve all text file from 1 to 3
tar -xvf abc.tar -> extract tar file
gzip abc.tar  ->zzip the tar file
















